                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="492543" author="adilger" created="Mon, 6 Apr 2026 19:24:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is related to multi-threading the &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs migrate&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; command as well, in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18455&quot; title=&quot;Make &amp;#39;lfs migrate&amp;#39; multi-threading&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18455&quot;&gt;LU-18455&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;An easy starting point would be to process multiple files in parallel on different threads, using the infrastructure from the multi-threaded &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs find&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There was also some work to move &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs migrate&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; over to use AIO/DIO in patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/56016&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/56016&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16789&quot; title=&quot;&amp;quot;lfs migrate&amp;quot; to use AIO/DIO or io_uring (kernel 5.1+)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-16789&quot;&gt;LU-16789&lt;/a&gt; utils: use AIO for &apos;lfs migrate&apos;&quot;) that could be used to do async checksum calculation as the IO for full raidsets of data complete, and then write out the resulting parity chunks.  That patch was only submitting async IO for a single file, rather than across files, which would be the logical next step.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
